pros:
A place where you can lead the change and take initiative;
A place where you are allowed to make mistakes and learn from them;
A good team of professionals to learn from;
Multiple development opportunities;
Flexibility in terms of working hours and attire (can be a little late at times and don't need to wear a suit);
Very appreciated benefits and perks, fun is part of the deal;
Employees are treated with fairness and have a voice;
An open door policy.

cons:
Since the only constant is change and some of the roads need to be built on the go, it can get tiring at one point, depending on your level of resilience. 
While innovating, sometimes it is harder to connect the dots and have a full overview of the bigger picture or a steady image - knowing what is next;
Not necessarily a Cons - Having a strong capability to influence others and be politically correct here are also factors working to one's benefit.
